> I've got to replace my 2 lower engine mount studs.  2L , dual carb
> engine (probably a 78?) mounted to a 5 ribbed tranny.  The studs on it
> are too short and have to be replaced.  I can get M10 X 85mm studs or 10
> X 82mm studs.  The problem is I don't know how far into the engine case
> the studs screw, so I can't measure.  It looks like the 82mm studs will
> work but I don't want to order them and then have to get the longer
> ones.  Any help appreciated.

Stan,

I think you need the longer studs, they are 97mm.

http://www.germansupply.com/xcart/customer/product.php?productid=16855

The 82mm ones are for upright engines, the 85mm are for upright and type 4
to 77.

